description: Enforce architecture boundaries between UI, context, services, and utils
alwaysApply: true
---

# Architecture Boundaries

- `screens` and `components` handle rendering and user interaction only.
- `context` owns shared app state, orchestration, and action APIs for UI layers.
- `services` own side effects (storage, network, platform I/O); keep them framework-light.
- `utils` contain pure deterministic logic (calculations, mappers, formatters).
- Do not access storage or network directly from screens/components.
- Keep domain contracts centralized in `src/types` and shared across layers.
